postcontent: Century Arms International Golani Sporter Project needs completed. (currently wearing a thread protector). -I planned to SBR this, so the gas system is set to continue to chop the barrel off right in front of the gas block. -Golani handguard was discarded, and a machine shop buddy machined a washer if you will, so i could put an AR15 hand guard and plate on it. -Currently wearing a hand fitted Magpul MOE mid-length FDE hand guard. -The original charging handle was machined off on the right side (because with the below listed rail/optic, you could not charge the weapon without losing skin). -Benelli M4 style rolling knob charging handle fitted onto the left side of the gun, and the dust cover cut out to accommodate. -PRI also mounted a rail section onto the dust cover, which I have a T1 clone currently mounted and zero'd (will be included). -I added a US Palm AK47 grip to this, and went through the hassle of fitting it to this.
